1
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:39,803
Get out.

2
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:30,062
I was working, man.

3
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,897
My dad didn't let me
answer the phone.

4
00:04:36,527 --> 00:04:37,903
That's how he is.

5
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:40,781
Him and his damn rules.

6
00:06:22,508 --> 00:06:23,842
They're still only making 2 trays a day.

7
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:26,053
Why isn't the place open yet?

8
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:28,472
They're so slow today.

9
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:32,518
It's already 8, Coughing Liu.

10
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:34,394
I've been trying to buy this for days.

11
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:39,483
The sun's already out
and about, man.

12
00:06:41,527 --> 00:06:42,653
We're coming, we're coming...

13
00:06:46,532 --> 00:06:47,407
Finally.

14
00:06:47,533 --> 00:06:48,408
Good morning, Mr. Li.

15
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:51,036
You guys are running late today.

16
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:52,287
The fire took a little longer today.

17
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:55,999
No need to rush.

18
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:56,750
Hurry up.

19
00:06:56,792 --> 00:06:57,543
We've been waiting forever.

20
00:06:57,584 --> 00:06:58,544
Look at all these people.

21
00:06:58,585 --> 00:06:59,711
I've been here all morning.

22
00:07:00,087 --> 00:07:00,921
Don't stand crowding around.

23
00:07:00,963 --> 00:07:01,964
Get in line,

24
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:02,840
or we're not selling.

25
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:04,091
Go on, now.

26
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:06,134
I've been here since dawn.

27
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:09,304
Every morning at opening,

28
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:11,014
the first person I see is you, Mr. Li.

29
00:07:11,515 --> 00:07:12,516
That's right.

30
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:13,767
Alright...

31
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:18,897
You know the drill.

32
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:20,482
What are they selling here?

33
00:07:20,524 --> 00:07:21,900
Look at all these people.

34
00:07:22,401 --> 00:07:23,318
This is delicious.

35
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,070
Everyone who visits this town comes here.

36
00:07:25,112 --> 00:07:26,363
Just get in line.

37
00:07:26,655 --> 00:07:27,823
Those behind the 7th person from the end,

38
00:07:27,865 --> 00:07:28,782
we can't serve you.

39
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:29,867
If you really want it,

40
00:07:29,908 --> 00:07:31,743
you'll have to come earlier tomorrow.

41
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:32,452
Those in the back missed out.

42
00:07:32,494 --> 00:07:32,953
Here we go, Mr. Li.

43
00:07:32,995 --> 00:07:33,745
Don't get too anxious.

44
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:34,538
Here we are.

45
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,542
Li, you old cripple.

46
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:41,503
There you are.

47
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:43,297
My daughter...

48
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:45,465
The first thing she asked for
after coming home

49
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:47,509
is your Crystal Cake.

50
00:07:47,843 --> 00:07:48,760
Great.

51
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:50,888
Don't drop it.

52
00:07:51,889 --> 00:07:53,348
Take it easy, Mr. Li.

53
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,855
I don't need change.

54
00:07:59,897 --> 00:08:01,607
I want 2 portions.

55
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:04,151
It's one per person.

56
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:06,862
Just sell me one more.

57
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:08,488
I can pay double.

58
00:08:08,906 --> 00:08:09,531
I'm afraid not.

59
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:10,616
Sorry,

60
00:08:11,033 --> 00:08:12,701
it's my dad's rule.

61
00:08:12,743 --> 00:08:14,411
Follow the rules, man.

62
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:18,916
It's just one more.

63
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:20,292
It's no big deal.

64
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:26,256
That's how it goes.

65
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:37,726
Thank you.

66
00:08:41,647 --> 00:08:42,940
What the hell?

67
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:43,607
I've been in this queue forever,

68
00:08:43,649 --> 00:08:45,067
and now you run out?

69
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:46,610
What kind of business
are you running here?

70
00:08:46,777 --> 00:08:47,611
That's right!

71
00:08:47,653 --> 00:08:48,987
I came all the way from Kunming

72
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,113
just to try your cake.

73
00:08:50,531 --> 00:08:52,115
Why can't you make more?

74
00:08:52,491 --> 00:08:54,993
Our shop's got plenty!

75
00:08:55,536 --> 00:08:56,161
Come on.

76
00:08:56,662 --> 00:08:57,454
Listen up.

77
00:08:57,496 --> 00:08:59,498
Our shop just opened today.

78
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,791
Fifteen yuan a portion.

79
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:02,209
Buy one, get one free.

80
00:09:02,251 --> 00:09:03,836
Buy as many as you want!

81
00:09:03,877 --> 00:09:04,837
We've got plenty!

82
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:05,379
That's right!

83
00:09:05,963 --> 00:09:06,630
And the flavor?

84
00:09:06,755 --> 00:09:07,631
Exactly the same.

85
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:08,423
Let's go.

86
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:09,132
It's just as good!

87
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:09,842
Let's go.

88
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:10,843
It's your lucky day.

89
00:09:11,593 --> 00:09:13,095
Forget them, they're all out.

90
00:09:20,102 --> 00:09:21,979
How shameless.

91
00:09:26,859 --> 00:09:28,819
Next, an update
on the Beijing Olympics.

92
00:09:28,861 --> 00:09:31,488
We're 60 days out
from the Opening Ceremony

93
00:09:31,530 --> 00:09:34,575
and 89 days
from the Beijing Paralympics.

94
00:09:34,616 --> 00:09:35,742
At 9 this morning,

95
00:09:35,784 --> 00:09:39,621
the relay of the torch began
in beautiful Yunnan.

96
00:09:39,663 --> 00:09:40,706
Ceremony attendees
observed a minute of silence

97
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:44,418
for victims of the Sichuan earthquake.

98
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,628
The relay's first stop is Kunming,
aka "Spring City."

99
00:09:52,384 --> 00:09:52,843
Let's go.

100
00:09:52,885 --> 00:09:53,719
Let's move out!

101
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:56,513
Out of the way!

102
00:09:59,016 --> 00:09:59,975
Watch out!

103
00:10:00,017 --> 00:10:01,518
Out of the way!

104
00:10:02,394 --> 00:10:04,605
Out of the way, please!

105
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:08,233
Watch out!

106
00:10:08,275 --> 00:10:10,277
Out of the way!

107
00:10:11,153 --> 00:10:13,488
Welcome to our grand opening!

108
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,866
Try it before you buy it!

109
00:10:15,908 --> 00:10:17,117
We've got delicious Crystal Cakes.

110
00:10:17,159 --> 00:10:18,160
Try it.

111
00:10:18,869 --> 00:10:19,912
Have a free sample.

112
00:10:20,412 --> 00:10:21,371
Welcome!

113
00:10:21,413 --> 00:10:23,665
Please have a free sample!

114
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:25,792
Welcome!

115
00:10:25,834 --> 00:10:28,086
Please have a free sample!

116
00:10:28,754 --> 00:10:29,213
Try it.

117
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:30,255
Welcome!

118
00:10:32,508 --> 00:10:33,550
Have a taste, ma'am.

119
00:10:33,592 --> 00:10:35,344
Please have a free sample!

120
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:37,513
This tastes terrible.

121
00:10:54,029 --> 00:10:55,239
My nephew, there you are.

122
00:11:07,376 --> 00:11:09,336
Seeing how your
knock-off shop is open,

123
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:12,756
I, as the 8th generation heir,
should pay a visit.

124
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:16,009
Huang Fei.

125
00:11:16,468 --> 00:11:17,135
Come here.

126
00:11:17,511 --> 00:11:18,720
Let them have a taste of this.

127
00:11:19,137 --> 00:11:20,973
Show them what a real
Crystal Cake tastes like.

128
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:21,849
Here,

129
00:11:22,641 --> 00:11:24,977
the real Crystal Cake.

130
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:26,103
Out of my sight.

131
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:27,938
Come on, have a free sample.

132
00:11:27,980 --> 00:11:29,398
Try it out, everyone.

133
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:31,233
Crystal Cake from Tong Shun Xiang,

134
00:11:31,275 --> 00:11:32,484
the one and only!

135
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:33,277
Come on.

136
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:34,778
Try this out.

137
00:11:38,532 --> 00:11:39,783
This one really is better.

138
00:11:40,868 --> 00:11:41,618
Good call!

139
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,036
Tong Shun Xiang's taste better,
after all.

140
00:11:45,163 --> 00:11:48,041
Every heir
to the Tong Shun Xiang legacy

141
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:51,336
must be able to replicate
the original flavor.

142
00:11:53,755 --> 00:11:55,591
You call yourself an heir,

143
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:58,260
but you still don't know
how to make it.

144
00:12:02,264 --> 00:12:03,974
The only man who can do it

145
00:12:04,766 --> 00:12:06,602
is your father.

146
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:18,989
Let's go.

147
00:12:21,783 --> 00:12:23,160
Best of luck to your shop!

148
00:12:25,162 --> 00:12:26,496
Happy opening!

149
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,375
Liu Jiansan! Huang Fei!

150
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:32,878
This isn't over yet!

151
00:14:57,856 --> 00:15:00,150
Those pirates are despicable!

152
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:02,319
When your dad
finally passes you the torch,

153
00:15:02,361 --> 00:15:03,612
open a few more branches.

154
00:15:03,904 --> 00:15:04,571
Seriously...

155
00:15:04,613 --> 00:15:06,156
You can crush those bastards.

156
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:08,617
I wish.

157
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:10,160
The problem is my dad.

158
00:15:10,911 --> 00:15:12,162
You know him.

159
00:15:12,496 --> 00:15:14,039
He only sells 2 trays a day.

160
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:16,792
And he won't give up
that old shop.

161
00:15:20,254 --> 00:15:22,506
I'm suffocating
in this dump of a village,

162
00:15:23,257 --> 00:15:25,259
doing dumb-ass things
like this every day.

163
00:15:26,635 --> 00:15:28,512
I should go out there
and see the world.

164
00:15:30,514 --> 00:15:31,515
Jiansan,

165
00:15:34,017 --> 00:15:36,019
let's work in the movies
with my cousin, Hu.

166
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:39,481
We can see celebrities
in the flesh

167
00:15:39,523 --> 00:15:41,149
and make lots of money.

168
00:15:45,112 --> 00:15:45,904
Really?

169
00:15:47,656 --> 00:15:49,658
As long as we stick together...

170
00:15:50,742 --> 00:15:51,994
You see all this?

171
00:15:52,536 --> 00:15:54,913
This is our world!

172
00:15:56,665 --> 00:15:58,250
Wake up, man.

173
00:15:58,292 --> 00:16:00,002
World domination?

174
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:19,438
Why are you in here?

175
00:16:21,273 --> 00:16:22,858
You didn't close the door.

176
00:16:24,610 --> 00:16:25,611
Get out.

177
00:16:26,153 --> 00:16:27,112
And close the door.

178
00:16:27,154 --> 00:16:29,114
You and your damn rules.

179
00:16:31,158 --> 00:16:31,742
What are you burning?

180
00:16:31,783 --> 00:16:32,618
What is that smell?

181
00:16:32,659 --> 00:16:33,410
Get out.

182
00:16:33,785 --> 00:16:34,536
Get out.

183
00:16:36,038 --> 00:16:36,747
What is all this?

184
00:16:36,788 --> 00:16:37,789
What are you doing?

185
00:16:38,248 --> 00:16:38,999
Stop.

186
00:16:44,713 --> 00:16:45,506
Get out.

187
00:16:51,512 --> 00:16:52,346
Dad...

188
00:16:53,138 --> 00:16:54,515
I've been at this for years.

189
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:57,726
I haven't slacked once.

190
00:16:58,143 --> 00:16:59,853
I wake up
at the crack of dawn every day.

191
00:17:00,145 --> 00:17:00,604
And all I do is knead dough.

192
00:17:00,646 --> 00:17:02,523
My hands are swollen from it,

193
00:17:03,023 --> 00:17:04,023
and there's even a scar.

194
00:17:05,526 --> 00:17:07,528
Yet, I still can't make it
as good as you.

195
00:17:08,403 --> 00:17:10,196
Everyone out there mocks me.

196
00:17:10,239 --> 00:17:11,906
They ask
how I can call myself an heir

197
00:17:12,241 --> 00:17:13,492
when I'm not qualified.

198
00:17:13,992 --> 00:17:15,993
Will you ever
pass the recipe to me?

199
00:17:17,412 --> 00:17:18,872
What are you burning anyway?

200
00:17:19,623 --> 00:17:20,374
Get out!

201
00:17:27,214 --> 00:17:29,091
I have nothing more
to pass to you.

202
00:17:34,388 --> 00:17:35,848
All you do is shut the door on me!

203
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:39,268
"Get out."

204
00:17:39,518 --> 00:17:40,978
Every single day!

205
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:43,438
We have the real thing,

206
00:17:43,605 --> 00:17:45,274
but we just make 2 trays a day.

207
00:17:45,732 --> 00:17:47,025
Look at Liu Tingzhong!

208
00:17:47,609 --> 00:17:49,111
He's making crappy knock-offs.

209
00:17:49,152 --> 00:17:50,529
and he's making a fortune.

210
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:51,905
What about me?

211
00:17:52,406 --> 00:17:53,657
I'm your son.

212
00:17:54,783 --> 00:17:55,993
Why can't you teach me?

213
00:17:56,034 --> 00:17:57,995
Let me make
some money of my own!

214
00:18:16,763 --> 00:18:17,639
I'm telling you.

215
00:18:18,515 --> 00:18:19,641
He's looking down on me

216
00:18:20,475 --> 00:18:21,727
because I couldn't get into college.

217
00:18:21,768 --> 00:18:23,812
That's why he's got me trapped here,

218
00:18:23,854 --> 00:18:24,855
following his every command.

219
00:18:27,649 --> 00:18:28,817
So it's decided.

220
00:18:28,859 --> 00:18:30,235
We have to leave this dump.

221
00:18:31,111 --> 00:18:32,029
Jiansan,

222
00:18:32,905 --> 00:18:34,156
what's mine...

223
00:18:34,489 --> 00:18:35,741
is yours.

224
00:18:36,366 --> 00:18:37,618
That's right, brother.

225
00:18:41,663 --> 00:18:42,247
It's all ours!

226
00:18:42,289 --> 00:18:43,624
Come on.

227
00:18:46,585 --> 00:18:47,461
Let's do this.

228
00:18:47,961 --> 00:18:48,837
It's been forever!

229
00:18:48,879 --> 00:18:49,963
We're a duo.

230
00:18:50,714 --> 00:18:52,090
Taking the music world by storm!

231
00:18:54,218 --> 00:18:55,969
"It doesn't matter

232
00:18:58,597 --> 00:19:00,974
who falls in love with the other."

233
00:19:02,726 --> 00:19:03,852
"It doesn't matter

234
00:19:06,438 --> 00:19:08,732
who wears out the other."

235
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:12,152
"The happiness we shared

236
00:19:13,737 --> 00:19:16,156
was merely a fleeting moment of beauty."

237
00:19:18,617 --> 00:19:20,244
"After the happiness..."

238
00:19:22,287 --> 00:19:23,163
That's Zhang Xiaoyue.

239
00:19:23,747 --> 00:19:25,123
She lives at the tea farm.

240
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:27,125
I hear she's pretty arrogant.

241
00:19:27,292 --> 00:19:28,877
Not even A Fu stands a chance.

242
00:19:30,587 --> 00:19:34,341
"Don't be so sure."

243
00:19:34,383 --> 00:19:35,217
"Right and wrong..."

244
00:19:35,259 --> 00:19:36,468
Xiaoyue.

245
00:19:36,510 --> 00:19:37,469
Look.

246
00:19:37,761 --> 00:19:39,096
My father went to Beijing on business

247
00:19:39,137 --> 00:19:40,264
and brought this back.

248
00:19:40,597 --> 00:19:41,557
An Olympic commemorative coin.

249
00:19:41,598 --> 00:19:42,474
Is he for real or is he just flirting?

250
00:19:42,516 --> 00:19:43,642
This set is special.

251
00:19:44,601 --> 00:19:46,061
It's a limited set.

252
00:19:46,103 --> 00:19:47,312
Only a few thousand in the whole country.

253
00:19:47,354 --> 00:19:48,146
My dad tells me that

254
00:19:48,188 --> 00:19:49,398
it'll be worth a fortune.

255
00:19:52,526 --> 00:19:53,277
What are you doing?

256
00:19:54,361 --> 00:19:56,280
Your pops is looking for you, man.

257
00:19:56,405 --> 00:19:57,531
What for?

258
00:19:57,906 --> 00:19:59,700
How should I know
what the village chief wants?

259
00:19:59,741 --> 00:20:01,243
Go on, hurry home.

260
00:20:02,119 --> 00:20:03,871
"It doesn't matter..."

261
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:09,543
Turn around, driver.

262
00:20:10,377 --> 00:20:11,086
Xiaoyue,

263
00:20:11,712 --> 00:20:13,297
I'll see you around.

264
00:20:13,338 --> 00:20:13,964
Move it, man.

265
00:20:14,006 --> 00:20:15,382
Your dad's waiting for you.

266
00:20:16,383 --> 00:20:17,342
Turn it around.

267
00:20:18,468 --> 00:20:19,386
Come on.

268
00:20:19,845 --> 00:20:20,846
Turn right.

269
00:20:22,472 --> 00:20:24,933
"Why make myself

270
00:20:24,975 --> 00:20:27,895
go through the pain
again and again."

271
00:20:29,438 --> 00:20:31,523
"It doesn't matter to me..."

272
00:20:55,756 --> 00:20:56,381
Who is it?

273
00:21:00,010 --> 00:21:00,636
It's me.

274
00:21:04,264 --> 00:21:05,766
What are you doing here?

275
00:21:08,644 --> 00:21:09,520
I...

276
00:21:11,230 --> 00:21:12,981
I was going up to your farm

277
00:21:13,023 --> 00:21:14,650
to get some firewood.

278
00:21:15,776 --> 00:21:17,402
In the middle of the night?

279
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:25,160
Didn't you know?

280
00:21:26,286 --> 00:21:27,621
Some firewood,

281
00:21:28,247 --> 00:21:29,540
can only be chopped at night.

282
00:21:30,874 --> 00:21:32,292
Who are you fooling?

283
00:21:33,377 --> 00:21:35,003
I know who you are.

284
00:21:35,754 --> 00:21:37,130
You make cake, right?

285
00:21:41,468 --> 00:21:42,886
You know a lot about me.

286
00:21:44,263 --> 00:21:45,806
If you like Crystal Cake,

287
00:21:45,848 --> 00:21:46,974
I can make them
for you every day.

288
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:50,519
You make the cakes?

289
00:21:54,314 --> 00:21:55,315
Yeah.

290
00:21:57,776 --> 00:21:59,403
I've been eating them all my life.

291
00:22:00,237 --> 00:22:01,738
I'm tired of them already.

292
00:22:03,907 --> 00:22:06,034
I can make you other flavors.

293
00:22:07,035 --> 00:22:08,120
What can you make?

294
00:22:08,537 --> 00:22:11,498
How about tiramisu,
strawberry pudding,

295
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:12,875
or chocolate brownie?

296
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:14,293
What are they?

297
00:22:14,668 --> 00:22:15,252
You...

298
00:22:19,131 --> 00:22:21,091
Oh, that's easy.

299
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,885
If you want some, I'll take you.

300
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:26,597
I can go by myself.

301
00:22:29,391 --> 00:22:31,768
I can be your
personal bodyguard, right?

302
00:22:32,603 --> 00:22:34,062
Anyway, how can that junk

303
00:22:34,104 --> 00:22:35,939
compare with our Crystal Cake?

304
00:22:36,773 --> 00:22:38,400
That junk you just mentioned...

305
00:22:38,775 --> 00:22:40,027
that's a cake, too, right?

306
00:22:40,277 --> 00:22:41,028
That's right.

307
00:22:41,528 --> 00:22:43,238
I've never heard of it.

308
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:45,657
Then how can you take me?

309
00:22:45,908 --> 00:22:47,367
I can learn.

310
00:23:18,398 --> 00:23:20,526
You go see your uncle Lee's daughter this afternoon.

311
00:23:22,903 --> 00:23:23,529
No.

312
00:23:23,737 --> 00:23:24,279
I have no time.

313
00:23:25,656 --> 00:23:26,281
You have to.

314
00:23:38,752 --> 00:23:41,004
"The railroad industry is changing rapidly."

315
00:23:41,255 --> 00:23:44,216
"Combustion engines
used to run 40 km per hour."

316
00:23:44,258 --> 00:23:47,135
"After the 6th campaign this year,"

317
00:23:47,511 --> 00:23:51,390
"all trains across the nation can now travel...

318
00:23:52,015 --> 00:23:53,892
on average of 120 km per hour."

319
00:23:54,393 --> 00:23:57,229
"Travel records have been broken repeatedly,

320
00:23:57,271 --> 00:24:00,732
"changing the travel industry as we know it."

321
00:24:00,774 --> 00:24:01,900
That's right.

322
00:24:05,404 --> 00:24:07,656
Do you think
I'll become a train attendant?

323
00:24:17,291 --> 00:24:19,168
If you fail,

324
00:24:20,752 --> 00:24:22,880
then stay
and run the shop with me.

325
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:27,259
Who'd want to run your shop?

326
00:25:12,387 --> 00:25:13,764
I see you have a girlfriend.

327
00:25:17,643 --> 00:25:19,853
If you're serious about her,

328
00:25:20,479 --> 00:25:22,564
then hurry up and marry her.

329
00:25:25,150 --> 00:25:26,485
Ask her family

330
00:25:26,527 --> 00:25:27,986
about what you need to propose.

331
00:25:28,028 --> 00:25:29,279
I'll take care of it.

332
00:25:29,988 --> 00:25:31,031
Dad...

333
00:25:31,490 --> 00:25:33,200
I'm only 23.

334
00:25:33,242 --> 00:25:34,868
What's the rush?

335
00:25:39,915 --> 00:25:42,125
Once you get married
and have a child,

336
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:44,002
the shop is yours.

337
00:25:49,091 --> 00:25:50,926
I can't even replicate your flavor.

338
00:25:50,968 --> 00:25:53,220
How am I qualified to take over?

339
00:26:09,403 --> 00:26:12,114
"If China Railway is like a vast ocean,"

340
00:26:12,364 --> 00:26:15,200
"I'll immerse into it as a drop of water."

341
00:26:15,242 --> 00:26:18,120
"I'll strive to work for our railway system."

342
00:26:18,287 --> 00:26:19,496
That's wrong.

343
00:26:19,538 --> 00:26:22,249
"You're the ocean, and I'm the drop of water."

344
00:26:22,291 --> 00:26:24,168
"I'll immerse into you."

345
00:26:41,393 --> 00:26:42,936
How romantic.

346
00:26:42,978 --> 00:26:44,313
How suave.

347
00:26:45,564 --> 00:26:47,441
What the hell do you two want?

348
00:26:47,482 --> 00:26:48,734
You looking for trouble?

349
00:26:49,484 --> 00:26:50,360
We need to talk to you.

350
00:26:50,402 --> 00:26:51,987
That's right. We need to talk.

351
00:27:08,253 --> 00:27:09,338
Jiansan's here.

352
00:27:18,889 --> 00:27:20,766
What do you want?
Come on.

353
00:27:21,266 --> 00:27:23,227
My dear nephew, I called you over

354
00:27:23,268 --> 00:27:24,603
because I care about you.

355
00:27:24,645 --> 00:27:25,812
That's enough.

356
00:27:25,854 --> 00:27:27,439
Cut the crap.

357
00:27:27,481 --> 00:27:29,024
I'm not even your biological nephew.

358
00:27:29,274 --> 00:27:31,276
Don't be so tactless.

359
00:27:32,903 --> 00:27:34,905
We share the same last name.

360
00:27:38,909 --> 00:27:41,370
Look, all these years...

361
00:27:41,411 --> 00:27:43,288
we've been making
the same Crystal Cake.

362
00:27:43,789 --> 00:27:46,667
We make it the same way
as your dad,

363
00:27:47,543 --> 00:27:49,378
but why is our flavor so different?

364
00:27:51,630 --> 00:27:54,216
Your father has the secret recipe.

365
00:27:56,385 --> 00:27:58,470
No matter how many times we ask,

366
00:27:58,512 --> 00:28:00,097
he won't tell anyone.

367
00:28:00,597 --> 00:28:02,099
He hasn't told you, either, right?

368
00:28:03,392 --> 00:28:05,769
Don't you want to know what it is?

369
00:28:11,525 --> 00:28:12,359
Look, your uncle

370
00:28:12,401 --> 00:28:15,404
knows that you need money.

371
00:28:16,029 --> 00:28:17,531
You got yourself a girlfriend, right?

372
00:28:18,782 --> 00:28:19,658
Here.

373
00:28:20,409 --> 00:28:21,285
Take this.

374
00:28:21,660 --> 00:28:24,037
Don't be shy. We're family.

375
00:28:29,418 --> 00:28:30,961
We should share

376
00:28:31,003 --> 00:28:33,255
the Tong Shun Xiang recipe,

377
00:28:33,755 --> 00:28:35,215
take it across the country

378
00:28:35,257 --> 00:28:37,384
and open a chain
so we can make a fortune.

379
00:28:38,635 --> 00:28:40,137
I'll let you decide,

380
00:28:40,512 --> 00:28:42,264
the size of your share.

381
00:29:16,131 --> 00:29:16,965
You're here.

382
00:29:17,007 --> 00:29:17,966
Come on in.

383
00:29:18,008 --> 00:29:18,884
Come on.

384
00:29:19,510 --> 00:29:20,385
How is it?

385
00:29:22,513 --> 00:29:23,263
Smells great.

386
00:29:26,016 --> 00:29:27,017
Smell this.

387
00:29:33,148 --> 00:29:34,191
Your son

388
00:29:34,233 --> 00:29:36,360
He's looking more
and more like you.

389
00:29:39,029 --> 00:29:40,906
Not quite there yet.

390
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:46,870
Let me know what else you need.

391
00:29:46,912 --> 00:29:49,414
Nothing but the best for you.

392
00:29:50,165 --> 00:29:54,711
(Chinese honey, Linxi marigold,
Uncle Wang)

393
00:30:01,635 --> 00:30:02,386
Get...

394
00:30:55,063 --> 00:31:00,152
(Steam for 20 minutes,
smoke for 5-7 minutes)

395
00:31:26,261 --> 00:31:27,346
This is good.

396
00:31:39,399 --> 00:31:41,151
It's still not the same.

397
00:31:43,779 --> 00:31:45,531
They're both good.

398
00:31:46,657 --> 00:31:48,408
You don't have to
make me feel better.

399
00:31:49,159 --> 00:31:51,286
I've been watching him
all my life,

400
00:31:52,037 --> 00:31:54,039
but he won't pass me
the entire recipe.

401
00:31:54,873 --> 00:31:56,416
What kind of a dad is he?

402
00:32:01,505 --> 00:32:03,257
At least you have a father.

403
00:32:04,132 --> 00:32:05,926
When I was old enough
to remember anything,

404
00:32:05,968 --> 00:32:07,719
my parents moved to Guangdong

405
00:32:07,761 --> 00:32:09,513
and left me with my uncle and aunt,

406
00:32:10,264 --> 00:32:12,808
promising to get me
when they earned enough.

407
00:32:12,850 --> 00:32:14,518
But they never came back.

408
00:32:15,769 --> 00:32:18,355
I've been working on the tea farm
since I was 6.

409
00:32:40,169 --> 00:32:41,378
Your hand.

410
00:32:43,130 --> 00:32:44,882
It's fine. Just a burn.

411
00:33:23,837 --> 00:33:24,963
Xiaoyue,

412
00:33:25,005 --> 00:33:27,466
something's come up.

413
00:33:27,508 --> 00:33:28,592
I can't take you home today.

414
00:33:28,634 --> 00:33:30,385
Show yourself out later.

415
00:34:43,417 --> 00:34:44,293
The process...

416
00:34:47,129 --> 00:34:48,130
The ingredients...

417
00:34:49,255 --> 00:34:51,132
they're all here, but...

418
00:34:54,094 --> 00:34:56,304
How's it going, Jiansan?

419
00:34:56,346 --> 00:34:58,015
Don't rush me, I'm working on it.

420
00:35:52,027 --> 00:35:53,028
Get out.

421
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:56,406
Get out.

422
00:36:17,636 --> 00:36:19,888
How much longer
are you hiding it from me?

423
00:36:27,855 --> 00:36:30,482
All our clansmen
say you have a secret recipe,

424
00:36:30,524 --> 00:36:32,276
but you won't pass it to me.

425
00:36:33,402 --> 00:36:34,361
How am I supposed to be the heir?

426
00:36:34,403 --> 00:36:36,154
Do you know how embarrassing
it is for me?

427
00:36:40,909 --> 00:36:43,036
I've taught you everything I can.

428
00:36:44,246 --> 00:36:47,374
Knowing and doing it
for real are very different.

429
00:36:47,666 --> 00:36:49,751
Why do you always kick me
out of the kitchen?

430
00:36:50,961 --> 00:36:52,462
What do you do in there?

431
00:36:57,259 --> 00:36:58,468
I get it.

432
00:37:00,345 --> 00:37:02,764
You never intend to pass me
the recipe, right?

433
00:37:03,974 --> 00:37:06,059
That's why I'll never
replicate your flavor.

434
00:37:06,101 --> 00:37:07,019
Am I right?

435
00:37:49,895 --> 00:37:53,273
I bought this at a bookstore
in the capital.

436
00:37:53,524 --> 00:37:54,942
Does this help?

437
00:37:54,983 --> 00:37:56,360
Of course it will.

438
00:37:56,401 --> 00:37:57,694
Will it really help?

439
00:37:57,736 --> 00:37:59,363
Of course, I'm sure of it.

440
00:37:59,404 --> 00:38:00,113
Are you sure?

441
00:38:00,155 --> 00:38:01,365
Just trust me.

442
00:38:01,406 --> 00:38:02,741
That's too much.

443
00:38:03,158 --> 00:38:04,576
Just look.

444
00:38:04,618 --> 00:38:05,619
Memorize all of this,

445
00:38:05,661 --> 00:38:07,246
and you'll pass for sure.

446
00:38:08,288 --> 00:38:09,540
Take your hands off her!

447
00:38:10,415 --> 00:38:12,292
You harass girls
in broad daylight now?

448
00:38:13,794 --> 00:38:14,878
Jiansan.

449
00:38:18,382 --> 00:38:20,384
Who said that you could touch her?

450
00:38:22,386 --> 00:38:23,345
Who gave you permission?!

451
00:38:23,387 --> 00:38:24,763
Xiaoyue asked me to come.

452
00:38:39,152 --> 00:38:41,238
Who the hell
do you think you are?

453
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:42,990
You just make pastries.

454
00:38:43,031 --> 00:38:44,408
You think you're good enough for her?

455
00:38:44,783 --> 00:38:47,244
You can't even make it
as good as your father.

456
00:38:47,286 --> 00:38:48,537
You don't know a damn thing.

457
00:38:58,881 --> 00:39:00,257
Get something straight, Liu Jiansan.

458
00:39:00,507 --> 00:39:02,050
Xiaoyue's mine.

459
00:39:02,092 --> 00:39:03,760
You're not good enough for her.

460
00:39:57,231 --> 00:39:58,232
Hey there, nephew.

461
00:39:59,107 --> 00:39:59,775
Your money.

462
00:40:00,150 --> 00:40:01,235
I don't want it.

463
00:40:02,277 --> 00:40:04,112
You want the secret recipe for Crystal Cake?

464
00:40:04,655 --> 00:40:05,572
I'll tell you the truth.

465
00:40:05,614 --> 00:40:06,406
It doesn't exist!

466
00:40:06,615 --> 00:40:08,158
Go find it yourself.

467
00:40:19,461 --> 00:40:20,629
What the hell are you looking at?

468
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,609
Let's eat.

469
00:41:18,729 --> 00:41:19,730
I want to move out.

470
00:41:26,653 --> 00:41:28,030
Let me have a cigarette.

471
00:42:04,650 --> 00:42:06,276
Don't you have anything to say?

472
00:42:18,914 --> 00:42:20,666
Look at this smoke.

473
00:42:22,793 --> 00:42:24,127
It can go wherever it wants.

474
00:42:24,169 --> 00:42:25,754
It doesn't answer to anyone.

475
00:42:35,764 --> 00:42:37,015
Our forefathers...

476
00:42:38,767 --> 00:42:40,769
None of them has ever met their grandchildren.

477
00:42:42,563 --> 00:42:44,439
That's why I named you Jiansan
("To see 3").

478
00:42:47,484 --> 00:42:50,279
I want to see 3 generations
under the same roof.

479
00:42:58,537 --> 00:43:00,372
I'm afraid I've disappointed you.

480
00:43:01,290 --> 00:43:03,292
Sorry that you have
such a disobedient son.

481
00:43:11,633 --> 00:43:14,136
Before she died,
your mother made me promise...

482
00:43:14,761 --> 00:43:16,096
that I wouldn't make you walk
in my footsteps.

483
00:43:16,138 --> 00:43:17,472
That's perfect.

484
00:43:18,891 --> 00:43:20,225
I'll never walk in your footsteps.

485
00:43:51,548 --> 00:43:52,049
Hello?

486
00:43:52,132 --> 00:43:53,467
Jiansan.

487
00:43:53,509 --> 00:43:54,468
Jiansan.

488
00:43:54,510 --> 00:43:56,386
Jiansan, listen to me, man.

489
00:43:57,346 --> 00:43:59,348
I'm so sorry, man.

490
00:43:59,389 --> 00:44:01,225
My mom said that if I left home,

491
00:44:01,266 --> 00:44:02,643
she'd poison herself.

492
00:44:02,851 --> 00:44:03,685
Look, man...

493
00:44:03,727 --> 00:44:05,812
Why don't you go ahead?

494
00:44:05,854 --> 00:44:07,064
I'll figure out how to join you later.

495
00:44:07,105 --> 00:44:07,940
How can you do this to me?

496
00:44:07,981 --> 00:44:09,399
Hello?

497
00:44:47,980 --> 00:44:50,107
Stop! It's time to meet your maker.

498
00:44:57,030 --> 00:44:58,782
Excuse me, is Hu...

499
00:45:03,871 --> 00:45:05,664
What do we do?
There's so many of them.

500
00:45:06,039 --> 00:45:07,040
Don't be afraid.

501
00:45:17,634 --> 00:45:18,385
Sorry, Director.

502
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:19,761
Cut! Cut!

503
00:45:20,137 --> 00:45:21,388
What's wrong with the sword?!

504
00:45:22,514 --> 00:45:23,348
Hu!

505
00:45:23,765 --> 00:45:24,892
Hu!

506
00:45:27,019 --> 00:45:27,853
Sorry, Director.

507
00:45:27,895 --> 00:45:29,021
I'll get it fixed in a minute.

508
00:45:29,229 --> 00:45:30,814
Get a new sword, Shuan Zi.
Quickly!

509
00:45:30,856 --> 00:45:31,982
Take a look at this, Dao.

510
00:45:32,900 --> 00:45:34,026
I'm so sorry.

511
00:45:34,651 --> 00:45:35,360
Hurry up!

512
00:45:35,402 --> 00:45:36,653
Thanks.

513
00:45:36,987 --> 00:45:37,613
It'll be fine.

514
00:45:37,654 --> 00:45:38,739
Don't worry.

515
00:45:38,780 --> 00:45:39,448
Hu.

516
00:45:39,489 --> 00:45:40,240
Here's the new one.

517
00:45:40,616 --> 00:45:41,116
No problem.

518
00:45:41,158 --> 00:45:41,742
Hu.

519
00:45:42,159 --> 00:45:42,868
Hu.

520
00:45:42,910 --> 00:45:43,702
I've finally found you.

521
00:45:43,744 --> 00:45:44,995
There you are, Jiansan.

522
00:45:45,162 --> 00:45:45,871
We're in the way.

523
00:45:45,913 --> 00:45:46,371
Let's go over there.

524
00:45:46,413 --> 00:45:47,039
Move it.

525
00:45:47,414 --> 00:45:48,415
We're ready, sir!

526
00:45:49,499 --> 00:45:50,501
Everyone in position!

527
00:45:50,542 --> 00:45:51,668
Let's do another take.

528
00:45:52,753 --> 00:45:53,504
Quan,

529
00:45:54,880 --> 00:45:56,215
didn't you check that
before the shoot?

530
00:45:57,132 --> 00:45:57,591
Seriously...

531
00:45:57,633 --> 00:45:58,634
It'll be fixed in a sec.

532
00:45:59,259 --> 00:45:59,885
Bro,

533
00:46:00,260 --> 00:46:01,887
this is how movies are made?

534
00:46:02,721 --> 00:46:03,639
This is nothing.

535
00:46:04,848 --> 00:46:06,683
Since you're here,
come work with us tomorrow.

536
00:46:06,725 --> 00:46:07,226
Sure.

537
00:46:07,267 --> 00:46:07,893
Oh, by the way,

538
00:46:08,268 --> 00:46:09,228
that's Suan Zi.

539
00:46:09,728 --> 00:46:11,396
Talk to him
if you have any questions.

540
00:46:11,438 --> 00:46:12,064
That's right.

541
00:46:12,231 --> 00:46:13,315
Hu is always busy.

542
00:46:13,357 --> 00:46:14,608
If you have questions about anything,

543
00:46:14,650 --> 00:46:15,526
just come to me.

544
00:46:15,984 --> 00:46:16,985
Nice to meet you.

545
00:46:51,144 --> 00:46:51,854
Everyone in position!

546
00:46:51,895 --> 00:46:52,980
We're about to shoot.

547
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:54,982
Jiansan, bring the wine over.

548
00:46:56,066 --> 00:46:57,025
Here it comes!

549
00:46:57,901 --> 00:46:58,735
Good.

550
00:47:00,612 --> 00:47:01,405
Get a move on.

551
00:47:02,614 --> 00:47:03,240
Action!

552
00:47:03,907 --> 00:47:04,783
In that case...

553
00:47:05,742 --> 00:47:06,618
Cheers.

554
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:14,251
Why is this real wine?!

555
00:47:14,293 --> 00:47:15,085
Cut! Cut!

556
00:47:15,127 --> 00:47:16,086
Props, what's going on?

557
00:47:16,128 --> 00:47:17,045
Sorry, sir.

558
00:47:17,087 --> 00:47:17,796
We'll fix it right away.

559
00:47:17,838 --> 00:47:19,047
Jiansan, change them to grape juice.

560
00:47:19,089 --> 00:47:20,507
Who said to use real wine?
Move it!

561
00:47:21,383 --> 00:47:22,718
What's wrong with you, man?

562
00:47:22,885 --> 00:47:23,719
Sorry.

563
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:24,678
I can't have alcohol!

564
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:25,846
I can't act
when I've had alcohol!

565
00:47:25,888 --> 00:47:26,471
I'm changing it right now.

566
00:47:26,513 --> 00:47:27,556
What's wrong with you?

567
00:47:27,598 --> 00:47:28,765
Sorry, just a second.

568
00:47:28,807 --> 00:47:29,224
I forgot to ask.

569
00:47:29,266 --> 00:47:30,267
Make-up!

570
00:47:35,105 --> 00:47:36,690
What the hell is this?!

571
00:47:36,732 --> 00:47:38,108
It's rock hard!

572
