580
00:47:45,240 --> 00:47:46,074
I'm so sorry.

581
00:47:46,116 --> 00:47:46,742
Go on.

582
00:47:46,783 --> 00:47:48,410
Go do the next shot.

583
00:47:48,911 --> 00:47:49,536
Get a new one.

584
00:47:49,912 --> 00:47:50,913
Sorry.

585
00:47:51,246 --> 00:47:51,872
Action!

586
00:47:58,378 --> 00:47:59,213
An action movie!

587
00:47:59,254 --> 00:47:59,880
This is awesome.

588
00:48:00,255 --> 00:48:01,006
Cut!

589
00:48:03,342 --> 00:48:04,468
Everyone in positions!

590
00:48:04,510 --> 00:48:05,344
Time to work.

591
00:48:05,385 --> 00:48:06,428
Stop eating, you two.

592
00:48:06,470 --> 00:48:07,513
Get a move on.

593
00:48:07,888 --> 00:48:09,473
Hurry up!

594
00:48:09,515 --> 00:48:10,849
Coming!

595
00:48:25,656 --> 00:48:27,032
Cut! Cut! Cut!

596
00:48:28,283 --> 00:48:29,284
You nitwit!

597
00:48:30,160 --> 00:48:31,662
Where did we get this actor?

598
00:48:32,412 --> 00:48:33,914
who doesn't know
how to use a rolling pin?

599
00:48:34,748 --> 00:48:35,666
What am I supposed to do?

600
00:48:36,792 --> 00:48:38,043
What do I do?!

601
00:48:40,504 --> 00:48:41,338
Director...

602
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:43,382
why don't I give it a try?

603
00:48:44,341 --> 00:48:46,385
Scene 18, shot 3, take 3.

604
00:49:11,368 --> 00:49:12,035
Jiansan...

605
00:49:12,494 --> 00:49:13,120
Bro.

606
00:49:13,787 --> 00:49:15,414
Nicely done.

607
00:49:16,039 --> 00:49:17,791
You really inherited your dad's skills.

608
00:49:18,542 --> 00:49:19,918
It was easy.

609
00:49:20,752 --> 00:49:23,088
I've been kneading dough all my life.

610
00:49:23,630 --> 00:49:25,090
It wasn't much.

611
00:49:27,384 --> 00:49:28,635
In our line of work,

612
00:49:29,469 --> 00:49:30,220
you endure,

613
00:49:30,888 --> 00:49:32,097
be ruthless,

614
00:49:32,389 --> 00:49:33,390
or get the hell out.

615
00:49:35,726 --> 00:49:37,436
Keep working for me,

616
00:49:37,477 --> 00:49:39,104
and I'll take you places.

617
00:49:40,939 --> 00:49:41,607
Hey, little girl,

618
00:49:42,107 --> 00:49:43,692
don't go easy on me.

619
00:49:43,734 --> 00:49:44,776
Put your back into it.

620
00:49:47,154 --> 00:49:48,739
This is my first time.

621
00:49:49,031 --> 00:49:50,032
It's nice.

622
00:49:50,365 --> 00:49:51,325
It's good, right?

623
00:49:51,366 --> 00:49:53,243
I don't feel that well.

624
00:49:53,869 --> 00:49:55,495
It means you have health problems.

625
00:50:07,633 --> 00:50:08,467
Hu.

626
00:50:13,889 --> 00:50:14,765
Hu?

627
00:50:17,267 --> 00:50:18,101
Hu!

628
00:50:19,853 --> 00:50:20,479
Hu!

629
00:50:20,687 --> 00:50:21,146
Get on the phone.

630
00:50:21,188 --> 00:50:22,064
Call an ambulance!

631
00:50:22,105 --> 00:50:22,564
Quickly!

632
00:50:22,606 --> 00:50:23,857
Hu!

633
00:50:24,191 --> 00:50:24,775
Hu!

634
00:50:25,025 --> 00:50:27,027
Mr. Liu, please reconsider.

635
00:50:27,361 --> 00:50:28,946
We've been working on this
for over 6 months.

636
00:50:28,987 --> 00:50:29,863
Hu's fallen ill,

637
00:50:29,905 --> 00:50:31,573
but we can still work.

638
00:50:31,615 --> 00:50:32,699
Am I right?

639
00:50:32,741 --> 00:50:33,742
That's right.

640
00:50:35,160 --> 00:50:36,745
Look, we have rules to abide by.

641
00:50:37,371 --> 00:50:39,039
We've already got a new crew.

642
00:50:40,624 --> 00:50:41,625
Sorry, man.

643
00:50:42,167 --> 00:50:42,751
Just go.

644
00:50:43,544 --> 00:50:44,837
Mr. Liu, please reconsider.

645
00:50:44,878 --> 00:50:45,754
Hey!

646
00:50:46,129 --> 00:50:47,422
Long time no see.

647
00:50:47,464 --> 00:50:48,298
Come on in.

648
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,299
Sit down.

649
00:50:49,341 --> 00:50:50,509
Thanks for coming in.

650
00:50:51,343 --> 00:50:52,511
Forget it, Jiansan.

651
00:50:53,095 --> 00:50:54,638
Don't you get it now?

652
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:58,100
I'll go talk to Li's team.

653
00:50:58,141 --> 00:50:59,977
I'll call you if there's work.

654
00:51:00,644 --> 00:51:01,478
Let's go.

655
00:51:30,883 --> 00:51:31,967
Noodle's ready.

656
00:51:33,010 --> 00:51:33,969
Morning!

657
00:51:34,011 --> 00:51:35,721
Morning, take a seat.

658
00:51:35,762 --> 00:51:36,638
A portion of dumplings, please.

659
00:51:40,726 --> 00:51:41,768
Right this way.

660
00:51:46,231 --> 00:51:49,026
Stop fighting!

661
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:54,281
Stop fighting!

662
00:51:55,032 --> 00:51:57,534
Stop fighting!

663
00:51:59,661 --> 00:52:02,956
I'm sorry.

664
00:52:02,998 --> 00:52:04,750
Who else wants some?!

665
00:52:15,719 --> 00:52:18,514
My food will conquer the world!

666
00:52:25,395 --> 00:52:27,022
Waitress!

667
00:52:27,064 --> 00:52:28,941
Where's my order? It's been forever.

668
00:52:28,982 --> 00:52:30,275
Coming right up.

669
00:52:47,251 --> 00:52:48,502
On TV just now...

670
00:52:48,544 --> 00:52:50,087
that was your hand, right?

671
00:52:59,388 --> 00:53:00,848
What's going on?

672
00:53:00,889 --> 00:53:02,099
I'm in a hurry.

673
00:53:02,140 --> 00:53:02,808
Hurry up!

674
00:53:02,850 --> 00:53:04,476
Sorry, I'll be right over.

675
00:53:07,354 --> 00:53:08,313
I'm off from work soon.

676
00:53:08,355 --> 00:53:09,648
Wait for me.

677
00:53:09,690 --> 00:53:10,941
I have something to tell you.

678
00:53:12,651 --> 00:53:13,944
Where are our wonton?

679
00:53:13,986 --> 00:53:15,112
Waitress, two more Baozi!

680
00:53:15,153 --> 00:53:16,405
Waitress,

681
00:53:17,155 --> 00:53:18,824
can I get some napkins?

682
00:53:18,866 --> 00:53:19,867
Sure thing.

683
00:53:21,159 --> 00:53:23,328
I told you, I'm in a hurry!

684
00:53:23,370 --> 00:53:24,329
Sorry to keep you waiting.

685
00:53:24,371 --> 00:53:25,706
Thanks.

686
00:53:25,747 --> 00:53:26,623
Waitress, my Baozi?

687
00:53:26,665 --> 00:53:27,624
Can you speed it up?

688
00:53:27,666 --> 00:53:29,251
The fried dough sticks?

689
00:53:30,002 --> 00:53:31,170
Napkins over here.

690
00:53:34,882 --> 00:53:36,842
Here are your wonton

691
00:54:11,877 --> 00:54:13,003
Thanks.

692
00:54:24,097 --> 00:54:24,890
When...

693
00:54:26,391 --> 00:54:28,268
When did you move out?

694
00:54:33,857 --> 00:54:35,275
After what happened last time...

695
00:54:45,285 --> 00:54:46,411
I'm sorry.

696
00:54:47,871 --> 00:54:49,164
It was my fault.

697
00:54:51,875 --> 00:54:53,919
I wanted to leave so badly.

698
00:54:56,588 --> 00:54:58,382
I asked A Fu

699
00:54:59,383 --> 00:55:01,635
to get exam information from his father.

700
00:55:06,139 --> 00:55:07,891
I know it must have hurt.

701
00:55:09,017 --> 00:55:10,978
I was selfish.

702
00:55:14,857 --> 00:55:15,816
I'm sorry.

703
00:55:24,116 --> 00:55:25,659
I've wanted to apologize all this time.

704
00:55:37,004 --> 00:55:39,131
I'm glad I ran into you.

705
00:55:40,257 --> 00:55:41,091
I really am...

706
00:56:38,482 --> 00:56:39,316
Cousin...

707
00:56:40,609 --> 00:56:41,360
Handling a huge shop by yourself

708
00:56:41,401 --> 00:56:43,153
must be exhausting.

709
00:56:43,612 --> 00:56:44,863
How's Jiansan doing?

710
00:56:46,281 --> 00:56:47,366
He's fine...

711
00:56:47,407 --> 00:56:48,367
He's fine...

712
00:56:48,784 --> 00:56:49,618
Look, cousin...

713
00:56:49,910 --> 00:56:51,161
This hundred-year-old shop

714
00:56:51,662 --> 00:56:52,996
shouldn't be your burden alone.

715
00:56:53,038 --> 00:56:54,540
Let's work together.

716
00:57:01,255 --> 00:57:02,965
That Tong Shun Xiang sign

717
00:57:06,468 --> 00:57:07,761
is one of a kind.

718
00:57:25,654 --> 00:57:26,530
It's Jiansan.

719
00:57:27,531 --> 00:57:28,115
Hi, Dad.

720
00:57:28,782 --> 00:57:29,366
Nothing much.

721
00:57:29,408 --> 00:57:31,243
Just called to say that I got married.

722
00:57:32,744 --> 00:57:33,662
And Xiaoyue's pregnant.

723
00:57:35,163 --> 00:57:36,123
Xiaoyue's pregnant.

724
00:57:36,623 --> 00:57:38,000
The signal here is weak.

725
00:57:38,625 --> 00:57:39,501
I can't hear you clearly.

726
00:57:39,543 --> 00:57:40,544
I have to go.
I'll talk to you later.

727
00:57:40,752 --> 00:57:41,545
Bye.

728
00:57:47,217 --> 00:57:48,635
How's your dad?

729
00:57:50,387 --> 00:57:51,096
He's fine.

730
00:57:51,138 --> 00:57:52,139
Totally fine.

731
00:57:52,764 --> 00:57:54,016
Still hanging on to that shop.

732
00:57:57,227 --> 00:57:58,395
Forefathers...

733
00:58:00,480 --> 00:58:01,064
Forefathers...

734
00:58:01,106 --> 00:58:03,400
3 generations of us
will be under one roof.

735
00:58:05,110 --> 00:58:06,612
Congrats on your marriage!

736
00:58:14,995 --> 00:58:16,246
Let's have another one.

737
00:58:17,789 --> 00:58:19,499
I learned so much from you

738
00:58:19,541 --> 00:58:21,543
while working on this film.

739
00:58:22,252 --> 00:58:23,795
All of us owe you so much.

740
00:58:23,837 --> 00:58:24,713
I mean it.

741
00:58:24,755 --> 00:58:25,756
It's a huge honor

742
00:58:26,006 --> 00:58:26,882
working for you.

743
00:58:27,341 --> 00:58:29,635
I can learn a lot from you.

744
00:58:32,721 --> 00:58:33,722
Hello?

745
00:58:34,515 --> 00:58:35,766
Really?

746
00:58:37,518 --> 00:58:40,145
I'm officially a dad!

747
00:58:46,026 --> 00:58:46,860
Say "grandpa."

748
00:58:47,736 --> 00:58:48,987
That's right, I'm "Grandpa."

749
00:58:55,035 --> 00:58:57,496
Grandpa's touching my little cheeks...

750
00:59:02,668 --> 00:59:04,044
Such strong arms.

751
00:59:04,753 --> 00:59:05,587
Let Grandpa hold you.

752
00:59:05,629 --> 00:59:06,964
You want to get up?

753
00:59:07,005 --> 00:59:08,632
Let Grandpa hold you.

754
00:59:13,220 --> 00:59:15,347
We're going up.

755
00:59:22,145 --> 00:59:23,230
You went way up.

756
00:59:23,355 --> 00:59:24,982
Give us a kiss.

757
00:59:29,278 --> 00:59:31,029
Oh, Grandpa's mustache must be itchy.

758
00:59:38,912 --> 00:59:40,163
Look at this.

759
00:59:41,790 --> 00:59:42,749
See this?

760
00:59:42,791 --> 00:59:44,168
This is Grandpa's Crystal Cake.

761
00:59:44,668 --> 00:59:45,627
See it?

762
00:59:45,669 --> 00:59:47,004
It's Crystal Cake from your Grandpa.

763
00:59:47,379 --> 00:59:48,630
"I want some!"

764
00:59:50,757 --> 00:59:51,466
Dad,

765
00:59:52,134 --> 00:59:53,760
she can only have milk.

766
00:59:54,636 --> 00:59:56,013
I'll just let her lick it.

767
00:59:56,346 --> 00:59:58,140
Just a lick.

768
01:00:01,351 --> 01:00:02,895
But you can't eat it.

769
01:00:09,610 --> 01:00:10,235
Dad...

770
01:00:10,277 --> 01:00:11,987
You must be tired.

771
01:00:12,029 --> 01:00:13,280
Let me hold her for a bit.

772
01:00:14,781 --> 01:00:16,033
Wenyan loves Grandpa.

773
01:00:16,909 --> 01:00:17,784
Bella...

774
01:00:18,243 --> 01:00:19,411
let Mommy hold you.

775
01:00:22,122 --> 01:00:23,165
What did you call her?

776
01:00:26,627 --> 01:00:28,962
That's the name Jiansan
and I gave her.

777
01:00:29,254 --> 01:00:30,130
Bella Liu.

778
01:00:30,506 --> 01:00:31,590
It sounds elegant, doesn't it?

779
01:00:32,257 --> 01:00:33,091
Come here.

780
01:00:40,974 --> 01:00:42,267
Wenyan.

781
01:00:43,894 --> 01:00:45,229
Grandpa's Wenyan.

782
01:00:45,854 --> 01:00:46,855
Come here.

783
01:00:47,731 --> 01:00:49,483
Look at this.

784
01:00:54,488 --> 01:00:55,739
Liu Wenyan.

785
01:00:57,282 --> 01:00:58,492
That's her name.

786
01:01:03,288 --> 01:01:04,498
Let's give her this name.

787
01:01:07,167 --> 01:01:10,879
"My name's going to be Wenyan."

788
01:01:12,339 --> 01:01:13,590
Wenyan...

789
01:01:14,007 --> 01:01:14,967
You have to scream,

790
01:01:15,008 --> 01:01:16,885
"Liu Jiansan!"

791
01:01:19,096 --> 01:01:21,014
"Come home!"

792
01:01:29,231 --> 01:01:30,107
Are you looking at this?

793
01:01:32,276 --> 01:01:33,652
You're home.

794
01:01:34,653 --> 01:01:35,529
Your dad's here.

795
01:01:36,029 --> 01:01:37,114
Look who's home?

796
01:01:39,241 --> 01:01:39,992
Dad...

797
01:01:40,033 --> 01:01:41,368
When did you get here, Dad?

798
01:01:42,160 --> 01:01:43,620
Why didn't you tell me?

799
01:01:43,662 --> 01:01:44,997
I could've gone to pick you up.

800
01:01:45,539 --> 01:01:46,665
No need for that.

801
01:01:47,791 --> 01:01:48,876
Get the good wine.

802
01:01:48,917 --> 01:01:50,252
I want to have a drink with dad.

803
01:01:51,128 --> 01:01:52,254
Look who's home?

804
01:01:54,381 --> 01:01:55,007
Bella.

805
01:01:55,465 --> 01:01:56,341
Look who's home?

806
01:01:57,134 --> 01:01:57,926
Bella.

807
01:01:57,968 --> 01:01:59,219
Daddy's home.

808
01:01:59,261 --> 01:02:00,095
Forget him.

809
01:02:01,388 --> 01:02:02,639
You're a father now.

810
01:02:03,390 --> 01:02:04,516
You shouldn't stay out so late.

811
01:02:07,477 --> 01:02:09,313
We just finished a huge film,

812
01:02:10,355 --> 01:02:12,608
so I took my guys out to celebrate.

813
01:02:13,275 --> 01:02:15,527
Your guys are more important
than your family?

814
01:02:17,905 --> 01:02:18,614
Listen to me,

815
01:02:18,655 --> 01:02:20,532
the most important thing for you right now

816
01:02:21,408 --> 01:02:22,659
is to take proper care

817
01:02:23,785 --> 01:02:25,996
of Wenyan here.

818
01:02:26,496 --> 01:02:27,164
Am I right?

819
01:02:27,789 --> 01:02:28,874
There, I taught him a lesson.

820
01:02:30,876 --> 01:02:31,793
Jiansan...

821
01:02:33,003 --> 01:02:34,254
It's from Dad.

822
01:02:36,089 --> 01:02:36,757
Come here.

823
01:02:37,883 --> 01:02:38,884
Rememeber...

824
01:02:39,510 --> 01:02:41,011
That's your name now...

825
01:02:41,386 --> 01:02:44,014
Liu Wenyan.

826
01:02:48,018 --> 01:02:49,520
The money's for you.

827
01:02:50,145 --> 01:02:51,813
I know living in the city is expensive.

828
01:02:53,690 --> 01:02:55,025
Give us a smile.

829
01:02:55,400 --> 01:02:56,527
Give us a smile.

830
01:02:57,277 --> 01:02:58,737
Give us a real smile.

831
01:02:59,988 --> 01:03:00,906
Where's that smile?

832
01:03:01,365 --> 01:03:02,533
There it is.

833
01:03:05,244 --> 01:03:07,037
It's time to get up

834
01:03:07,538 --> 01:03:08,789
and look around.

835
01:03:12,793 --> 01:03:14,545
You've got a baby daughter.

836
01:03:16,505 --> 01:03:18,632
You can't let Xiaoyue
raise her by herself.

837
01:03:20,133 --> 01:03:21,760
You have to spend time with them.

838
01:03:24,513 --> 01:03:26,306
I've got a lot of guys
working for me.

839
01:03:26,348 --> 01:03:27,891
They depend on me
to make a living.

840
01:03:31,603 --> 01:03:32,938
It's not easy for me,
you know.

841
01:03:37,276 --> 01:03:39,778
If it's so hard
to make money out there...

842
01:03:42,531 --> 01:03:43,657
Come home.

843
01:03:47,411 --> 01:03:49,371
Take over the shop.

844
01:03:50,163 --> 01:03:52,040
I'll teach you everything
you need to know.

845
01:03:53,917 --> 01:03:55,919
The shop is as good as yours.

846
01:04:04,970 --> 01:04:07,139
You didn't want to teach me
back then...

847
01:04:08,891 --> 01:04:10,517
And now I don't need it anymore.

848
01:04:14,146 --> 01:04:16,440
I know what I'm doing for once.

849
01:04:18,650 --> 01:04:20,777
Everything I do now...

850
01:04:21,528 --> 01:04:22,905
I earned it all by myself.

851
01:04:26,658 --> 01:04:28,035
I'm doing just fine.

852
01:04:36,793 --> 01:04:38,420
I see...

853
01:04:41,089 --> 01:04:42,216
Think about it some more.

854
01:04:43,217 --> 01:04:44,718
Don't make a decision you'll regret.

855
01:04:50,766 --> 01:04:52,017
I don't regret a thing.

856
01:06:10,137 --> 01:06:12,097
Mommy...

857
01:06:12,139 --> 01:06:13,515
Wenyan.

858
01:06:22,608 --> 01:06:24,151
Mommy...

859
01:06:26,528 --> 01:06:28,030
Mommy...

860
01:06:33,285 --> 01:06:34,870
Mommy...

861
01:06:46,215 --> 01:06:47,466
You're Liu Wenyan's parent?

862
01:06:47,508 --> 01:06:48,008
I am.

863
01:06:48,133 --> 01:06:49,343
Come on in.

864
01:06:53,263 --> 01:06:54,640
Your child has infantile pneumonia.

865
01:06:55,015 --> 01:06:57,267
There's a large area of infection in her lungs.

866
01:06:57,518 --> 01:06:59,019
If we can't get the infection under control,

867
01:06:59,394 --> 01:07:00,979
she'll need a ventilator.

868
01:07:55,367 --> 01:07:57,244
We got another overdue notice.

869
01:07:58,412 --> 01:07:59,788
This money pit is bottomless.

870
01:08:01,164 --> 01:08:02,666
When I finish this film,

871
01:08:03,375 --> 01:08:04,626
we'll have some money come in.

872
01:08:14,761 --> 01:08:16,138
Just wait a little longer.

873
01:08:19,850 --> 01:08:21,350
Her illness can't wait.

874
01:08:21,894 --> 01:08:23,270
She's a child.

875
01:08:24,854 --> 01:08:26,982
Why does she have to endure this?

876
01:08:29,984 --> 01:08:32,112
If only I could take her place...

877
01:09:28,877 --> 01:09:30,045
2 per customer!

878
01:09:33,465 --> 01:09:35,133
I want 2 today.

879
01:09:41,265 --> 01:09:42,015
Thanks.

880
01:09:44,893 --> 01:09:46,144
2, please.

881
01:09:47,270 --> 01:09:48,354
Thanks.

882
01:09:49,731 --> 01:09:50,941
I'll take 2.

883
01:09:52,609 --> 01:09:53,777
Ten yuan's your change.

884
01:10:32,983 --> 01:10:34,026
There's no limit anymore.

885
01:10:34,067 --> 01:10:35,360
That's great.

886
01:10:40,240 --> 01:10:41,283
Come on, Li.

887
01:10:41,658 --> 01:10:42,367
How many?

888
01:10:42,409 --> 01:10:43,327
No limit?

889
01:10:43,368 --> 01:10:44,661
As many as you want.

890
01:10:48,290 --> 01:10:49,291
I'll take 3.

891
01:11:06,767 --> 01:11:07,392
Hello?

892
01:11:07,643 --> 01:11:08,352
Dad.

893
01:11:08,644 --> 01:11:10,145
Wenyan's operation was a success.

894
01:11:10,521 --> 01:11:12,147
It took a little long,

895
01:11:12,189 --> 01:11:13,315
but she'll be fine.

896
01:11:13,607 --> 01:11:16,026
The doctor says
she just need some time to recover.

897
01:11:17,486 --> 01:11:18,654
That's good.

898
01:11:19,154 --> 01:11:20,489
Jiansan's here, too.

899
01:11:20,531 --> 01:11:21,657
Don't worry.

900
01:11:22,866 --> 01:11:23,909
Sure.

901
01:11:24,618 --> 01:11:25,869
She's fine now.

902
01:11:46,640 --> 01:11:47,599
You're home!

903
01:11:47,641 --> 01:11:48,642
Daddy!

904
01:11:49,351 --> 01:11:50,477
Come here, baby.

905
01:11:50,519 --> 01:11:51,228
Let me see you.

906
01:11:52,729 --> 01:11:54,606
My Wenyan's all grown up.

907
01:11:55,607 --> 01:11:56,567
Did you miss Daddy?

908
01:11:56,608 --> 01:11:57,401
I did.

909
01:11:57,860 --> 01:11:59,653
Were you good to Mommy while I was gone?

910
01:12:00,779 --> 01:12:03,282
Were you?

911
01:12:04,533 --> 01:12:06,159
I need to unpack.

912
01:12:08,537 --> 01:12:10,289
Come eat something first.

913
01:12:11,665 --> 01:12:13,292
Start without me.

914
01:12:19,131 --> 01:12:20,465
Are you glad that Daddy's home?

915
01:12:20,507 --> 01:12:21,717
I am!

916
01:12:22,509 --> 01:12:24,261
Get Daddy a bowl of rice.

917
01:12:31,894 --> 01:12:33,395
Mommy, come here.

918
01:12:41,361 --> 01:12:42,988
You just got home,
and you're leaving again?

919
01:12:45,282 --> 01:12:46,408
I just got a phone call.

920
01:12:46,909 --> 01:12:48,035
A big shot director

921
01:12:48,160 --> 01:12:49,411
just fired his props team.

922
01:12:49,995 --> 01:12:51,747
I need to bring a few guys
over there right now.

923
01:12:55,542 --> 01:12:56,793
Daddy.

924
01:12:57,419 --> 01:12:58,921
Don't leave.

925
01:13:01,215 --> 01:13:02,007
Come here.

926
01:13:05,344 --> 01:13:06,678
Daddy will be home soon.

927
01:13:06,720 --> 01:13:07,554
Alright?

928
01:13:07,596 --> 01:13:08,430
When I come home,

929
01:13:08,472 --> 01:13:09,848
I'll buy you something nice to eat.

930
01:13:10,641 --> 01:13:11,975
Listen to Mommy
and be a good girl.

931
01:13:12,017 --> 01:13:13,352
Okay? Be good.

932
01:13:17,481 --> 01:13:19,983
We haven't sat down
for a meal in 6 months.

933
01:13:20,651 --> 01:13:22,152
At least sit down for this one.

934
01:13:22,277 --> 01:13:23,779
It won't take much time.

935
01:13:25,155 --> 01:13:26,907
I still have things to talk to you about.

936
01:13:27,407 --> 01:13:28,659
We can talk when I'm back.

937
01:13:31,620 --> 01:13:33,038
Wenyan has to start school soon.

938
01:13:35,791 --> 01:13:37,668
She's not eligible for public school.

939
01:13:38,043 --> 01:13:39,628
And private school is too expensive.

940
01:13:43,882 --> 01:13:44,842
I got it.

941
01:13:44,883 --> 01:13:46,009
I'll think of something.

942
01:13:48,387 --> 01:13:50,013
You don't have to work like this.

943
01:13:51,265 --> 01:13:52,766
I can find work, too.

944
01:13:53,600 --> 01:13:55,227
Then we can spend more time together

945
01:13:55,269 --> 01:13:56,645
as a family.

946
01:13:59,982 --> 01:14:00,858
Jiansan!

947
01:14:02,526 --> 01:14:03,277
Jiansan!

948
01:14:05,904 --> 01:14:07,281
I'll be right there!

949
01:14:12,786 --> 01:14:14,288
Let's drop this for now.

950
01:14:14,496 --> 01:14:15,873
Wait until I finish this job

951
01:14:15,914 --> 01:14:17,291
and make some money.

952
01:14:17,916 --> 01:14:19,918
Then I can find a kindergarten
for Wenyan.

953
01:14:20,169 --> 01:14:22,421
And we'll go on a family trip, okay?

954
01:14:25,757 --> 01:14:27,259
You always say that.

955
01:14:29,094 --> 01:14:30,762
You just make empty promises.

956
01:14:32,014 --> 01:14:33,765
Even if that day really comes,

957
01:14:34,224 --> 01:14:35,601
we might not be here anymore.

958
01:14:36,143 --> 01:14:37,519
Is it really worth it?

959
01:14:41,356 --> 01:14:43,692
You think I don't want
to be with my family?

960
01:14:44,193 --> 01:14:45,944
I bust my ass out there every day

961
01:14:45,986 --> 01:14:48,113
just so I can make us some money.

962
01:14:49,156 --> 01:14:50,115
You should understand that.

963
01:14:50,157 --> 01:14:52,534
I can't do as I please.

964
01:14:57,873 --> 01:14:58,999
Jiansan,

965
01:14:59,166 --> 01:15:00,501
I've been thinking.

966
01:15:00,876 --> 01:15:03,128
Maybe we can take Wenyan home.

967
01:15:03,504 --> 01:15:05,088
You won't have to work so hard.

968
01:15:06,131 --> 01:15:07,257
Like your dad said...

969
01:15:08,509 --> 01:15:10,385
Tong Shun Xiang is ours if we want it.

970
01:15:11,261 --> 01:15:12,638
You can go by yourself.

971
01:15:13,138 --> 01:15:14,515
I'm staying here.

972
01:15:15,098 --> 01:15:17,142
I worked hard to build a life here.

973
01:15:19,228 --> 01:15:21,188
But we're nothing here.

974
01:15:34,660 --> 01:15:35,536
Hello?

975
01:15:46,839 --> 01:15:47,840
Mommy!

976
01:15:48,340 --> 01:15:49,258
It's a cow!

977
01:15:52,261 --> 01:15:53,595
Doesn't that colorful cloud look beautiful?

978
01:15:53,720 --> 01:15:55,097
It does.

979
01:16:01,019 --> 01:16:02,354
Come on, let Daddy hold you.

980
01:16:07,401 --> 01:16:08,277
Wenyan,

981
01:16:08,527 --> 01:16:10,946
this is your parents' hometown. Gorgeous?

982
01:16:10,988 --> 01:16:12,072
Gorgeous.

983
01:16:12,114 --> 01:16:13,240
Look at that.

984
01:16:22,791 --> 01:16:23,750
Are you hungry?

985
01:16:25,627 --> 01:16:26,503
There are flower cakes over there.

986
01:16:26,545 --> 01:16:28,255
I'll buy some for you later, okay?

987
01:16:29,256 --> 01:16:30,215
It's an herbal medicine.

988
01:16:30,257 --> 01:16:31,466
You can make tea with it.

989
01:16:31,508 --> 01:16:32,885
It's great for detox.

990
01:16:33,260 --> 01:16:34,261
Take a look.

991
01:16:34,761 --> 01:16:35,846
You can take a whiff of it for yourself.

992
01:16:36,388 --> 01:16:37,222
We also have this.

993
01:16:37,264 --> 01:16:38,140
Take a look.

994
01:16:38,515 --> 01:16:39,766
Give me that.

995
01:16:41,226 --> 01:16:41,852
Take this.

996
01:16:42,769 --> 01:16:43,729
Here's what I suggest...

997
01:16:43,770 --> 01:16:45,314
Come take a tour of our factory.

998
01:16:45,856 --> 01:16:47,983
We can have some tea.

999
01:17:00,037 --> 01:17:01,413
Dad.
(Temporarily Closed)

1000
01:17:01,914 --> 01:17:03,290
Where are we?

1001
01:17:05,667 --> 01:17:07,044
This...

1002
01:17:08,670 --> 01:17:09,963
This is our home.

1003
01:17:11,131 --> 01:17:12,466
We are home now.

1004
01:17:24,102 --> 01:17:25,729
Grandpa!

1005
01:17:28,732 --> 01:17:30,317
Wenyan...

1006
01:17:32,236 --> 01:17:33,028
You're home.

1007
01:17:33,487 --> 01:17:34,488
You're so lazy.

1008
01:17:34,530 --> 01:17:36,615
Why don't you get out of bed?

1009
01:17:40,786 --> 01:17:41,787
Grandpa

1010
01:17:42,371 --> 01:17:43,872
didn't know you are coming back

1011
01:17:44,665 --> 01:17:45,999
If I'd known you were coming home...

1012
01:17:46,041 --> 01:17:47,209
I would've woken up

1013
01:17:47,251 --> 01:17:49,211
to pick you and your parents up.

1014
01:17:49,253 --> 01:17:51,296
I got you some flowers.

1015
01:17:55,717 --> 01:17:57,970
They smell so nice.

1016
01:17:58,762 --> 01:17:59,972
Your grandpa's tired.

1017
01:18:00,013 --> 01:18:01,139
He needs some rest,

1018
01:18:01,515 --> 01:18:02,099
okay?

1019
01:18:02,140 --> 01:18:03,141
Okay.

1020
01:18:21,034 --> 01:18:22,160
You're home.

1021
01:18:27,791 --> 01:18:28,876
Look at you.

1022
01:18:28,917 --> 01:18:30,294
What were you trying to prove?

1023
01:18:31,253 --> 01:18:32,754
You broke your own rule

1024
01:18:33,630 --> 01:18:35,132
and got yourself sick.

1025
01:18:36,216 --> 01:18:37,718
Screw the rules...

1026
01:18:47,019 --> 01:18:47,978
Dad...

1027
01:18:49,813 --> 01:18:51,565
Let's go see a doctor in the city.

1028
01:18:54,067 --> 01:18:55,986
As long as I can see Wenyan...

1029
01:18:59,281 --> 01:19:00,532
I'm happy.

1030
01:19:28,018 --> 01:19:31,647
"All alone in a strange land,
a lonely stranger am I."

1031
01:19:31,688 --> 01:19:35,526
"Thoughts of my kindred redouble
on every festive day."

1032
01:19:35,567 --> 01:19:39,488
"From afar I know, O brothers,
where in the hills we'd be,"

1033
01:19:39,530 --> 01:19:42,741
"each wearing a spray of dogwood,
all but the one away."

1034
01:19:43,158 --> 01:19:44,117
Good.

1035
01:19:45,869 --> 01:19:46,787
Very good.

1036
01:19:48,038 --> 01:19:49,248
Hai!

1037
01:20:01,718 --> 01:20:03,387
Little Wenyan...

1038
01:21:21,882 --> 01:21:23,091
Dad...

1039
01:21:23,133 --> 01:21:24,635
Let me do it.

1040
01:21:30,098 --> 01:21:31,558
Wenyan...

1041
01:21:31,600 --> 01:21:32,601
Let's go.

1042
01:21:37,731 --> 01:21:38,565
Little bunny

1043
01:21:38,607 --> 01:21:40,442
hopping up and down, up and down.

1044
01:21:40,484 --> 01:21:42,486
All the way to your mustache.

1045
01:21:42,528 --> 01:21:43,487
It's so itchy!

1046
01:21:43,529 --> 01:21:45,072
Running all the way up your head.

1047
01:21:45,113 --> 01:21:46,490
It smells!

1048
01:21:54,665 --> 01:21:55,541
Dad.

1049
01:24:22,813 --> 01:24:24,189
Hey, Jiansan,

1050
01:24:24,481 --> 01:24:25,649
I got a huge job.

1051
01:24:25,691 --> 01:24:26,733
It's Zhang's film.

1052
01:24:27,317 --> 01:24:28,443
Come back right now.

1053
01:24:28,485 --> 01:24:30,028
We need you to sign the contract.

1054
01:24:31,029 --> 01:24:31,738
Hello?

1055
01:24:38,412 --> 01:24:39,872
They're rushing you back again?

1056
01:25:08,483 --> 01:25:10,402
Your dad, Tingshen,

1057
01:25:10,652 --> 01:25:11,904
was an upright man.

1058
01:25:13,030 --> 01:25:14,907
He was forgiving and benevolent.

1059
01:25:16,366 --> 01:25:17,993
But he left us way too early.

1060
01:25:19,494 --> 01:25:21,496
He worked himself to the bone.

1061
01:25:24,291 --> 01:25:27,169
After he had Jiansan,

1062
01:25:27,419 --> 01:25:29,129
he insisted on only making
2 trays a day.

1063
01:25:29,922 --> 01:25:31,840
But he eventually took away the limit.

1064
01:25:35,719 --> 01:25:36,970
Still, other than him,

1065
01:25:38,222 --> 01:25:40,307
no other heir
of the Tong Shun Xiang clan

1066
01:25:40,349 --> 01:25:42,142
got to see 3 generations
under one roof.

1067
01:25:42,893 --> 01:25:43,977
None of them

1068
01:25:44,144 --> 01:25:46,063
lived past 60 years old.

1069
01:25:47,606 --> 01:25:49,441
Is there really some kind of curse?

1070
01:25:57,533 --> 01:25:59,660
He did get to see
his granddaughter, though.

1071
01:26:00,619 --> 01:26:01,995
He must've been grateful for that.

1072
01:26:14,967 --> 01:26:16,343
What's Wenyan doing here?

1073
01:26:23,350 --> 01:26:25,519
A girl can't be in the family register.

1074
01:26:26,770 --> 01:26:27,938
This can't be right.

1075
01:26:28,313 --> 01:26:31,191
The Liu's only pass their skills
to male heirs.

1076
01:26:32,818 --> 01:26:34,319
Why is the ninth generation
there already?

1077
01:26:34,361 --> 01:26:35,737
You're going to pass it to her?

1078
01:26:35,779 --> 01:26:36,613
Are you serious?

1079
01:28:01,657 --> 01:28:04,368
"March 6, 1985."

1080
01:28:05,035 --> 01:28:06,036
"Today,

1081
01:28:06,495 --> 01:28:07,996
my son was born."

1082
01:28:08,539 --> 01:28:09,665
"At just 4 catties,

1083
01:28:10,040 --> 01:28:11,291
he was a little small."

1084
01:28:13,126 --> 01:28:14,586
"In the Liu clan,

1085
01:28:14,628 --> 01:28:17,256
the clan elder inherits
the Crystal Cake recipe."

1086
01:28:18,382 --> 01:28:20,843
"In the making of Crystal Cakes,

1087
01:28:20,884 --> 01:28:22,094
the most important step

1088
01:28:22,719 --> 01:28:25,180
is WENYAN (to inhale the smoke)."

1089
01:28:25,597 --> 01:28:29,476
"To seize the moment
the special wood gives off its aroma,

1090
01:28:30,143 --> 01:28:31,979
I have to sit in front of the stove

1091
01:28:32,396 --> 01:28:33,856
and keep inhaling the smoke away."

1092
01:28:39,403 --> 01:28:40,529
"Inhaling smoke

1093
01:28:41,113 --> 01:28:43,407
is incredibly damaging
to one's health."

1094
01:28:44,867 --> 01:28:46,159
"But to keep up our tradition,

1095
01:28:46,535 --> 01:28:48,370
I have to keep making
Crystal Cakes

1096
01:28:48,787 --> 01:28:51,248
even if it kills me."

1097
01:28:51,999 --> 01:28:53,667
"When my son is grown,

1098
01:28:54,418 --> 01:28:56,879
he'll repeat the fate
of my forefathers and me."

1099
01:28:57,421 --> 01:28:59,590
Once you get married
and have a child,

1100
01:28:59,631 --> 01:29:01,508
the shop is yours.

1101
01:29:02,634 --> 01:29:04,386
"That's why I gave him the name

1102
01:29:04,720 --> 01:29:05,971
Jiansan (to see 3 generations)."

1103
01:29:06,263 --> 01:29:08,891
"I hope to live long enough
to see his children."

1104
01:29:10,601 --> 01:29:11,894
"That's why I've decided the following:"

1105
01:29:12,728 --> 01:29:13,645
"One..."

1106
01:29:13,770 --> 01:29:16,481
"Without damaging my health,

1107
01:29:16,857 --> 01:29:19,067
find a way to replicate

1108
01:29:19,109 --> 01:29:20,903
the flavor of the Crystal Cake."

1109
01:29:22,654 --> 01:29:23,405
"Two..."

1110
01:29:23,989 --> 01:29:25,908
"To ensure that I'll see his children,

1111
01:29:26,158 --> 01:29:27,367
I've decided

1112
01:29:27,409 --> 01:29:29,620
to limit daily production

1113
01:29:29,745 --> 01:29:31,163
to just 2 trays."

1114
01:29:31,914 --> 01:29:32,664
I'm afraid not.

1115
01:29:32,789 --> 01:29:33,999
Sorry,

1116
01:29:34,041 --> 01:29:35,667
it's my dad's rule.

1117
01:29:38,921 --> 01:29:39,671
"Three..."

1118
01:29:40,130 --> 01:29:41,715
"From now on,

1119
01:29:41,757 --> 01:29:44,635
I'll record my progress

1120
01:29:45,135 --> 01:29:47,262
until I find a new recipe

1121
01:29:47,638 --> 01:29:49,139
that I can pass to Jiansan."

1122
01:29:52,392 --> 01:29:53,268
Get out.

1123
01:30:00,108 --> 01:30:02,861
"June 19, 1990."

1124
01:30:03,278 --> 01:30:04,363
"A rainy day."

1125
01:30:05,531 --> 01:30:07,908
"Jiansan's mother has died."

1126
01:30:08,992 --> 01:30:11,620
"I can't believe that she left before me."

1127
01:30:13,163 --> 01:30:14,414
"Before she passed,

1128
01:30:14,915 --> 01:30:17,417
I told her the secret of the Crystal Cake."

1129
01:30:18,418 --> 01:30:19,419
"She asked me not to

1130
01:30:19,795 --> 01:30:22,798
let Jiansan walk in my footsteps

1131
01:30:22,840 --> 01:30:24,633
and endure the same fate."

1132
01:30:25,384 --> 01:30:27,344
That's why I'll never replicate your flavor.

1133
01:30:27,886 --> 01:30:28,637
Am I right?

1134
01:30:56,164 --> 01:30:59,042
"October 5, 2010. A sunny day."

